"I cannot quite believe this video is actually produced by BBC. It is not just lopsided praise; it is a dangerously incomplete story. By ignoring the context, the bankruptcies, the colossal waste, and the unsustainable economics of the price war, this video presents a fiction. It mistakes the feverish, chaotic, and wasteful symptoms of a state-driven industrial campaign for a story of organic, sustainable innovation. It celebrates the handful of survivors standing on a mountain of failed companies and wasted capital, and presents it as the future, willfully ignorant of the unsustainable foundation upon which that future is built. Ask ChatGPT to explain ""_____"" in English to you, please."	Neutral	Negative
